        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 2:47PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Frankenmuth to near
New Lothrop to Lennon. Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Flushing, Frankenmuth, Birch Run, New Lothrop, Montrose, and
Lennon around 250 PM EDT.
Vassar around 300 PM EDT.
Reese, and Beecher around 305 PM EDT.
Clio and Mount Morris around 310 PM EDT.
Fairgrove around 315 PM EDT.
Caro around 320 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include East Dayton, Arthur,
Tuscola, Colling, Burt, Ellington, Gera, Gilford, Layton Corners, and
Richville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
